                    "company": "KuiperCompagnons",
                    "description": "As a project leader at KuiperCompagnons within the International Cluster, Chris had a particular focus on both detailed landscape design / implementation as well as strategic urban projects. Noteworthy projects include Aerocity New Delhi, India for the realisation of a high-end hospitality district landscape and commercialisation project at the international airport. In Jakarta, Indonesia, Chris was part of the team preparaing a master plan for safe guarding the future of the city as it struggles with flood risks and the chronic need for urban revitalisation.\n\nInspired by the regeneration of his home city of Manchester, England, Chris trained as a Landscape Architect at the Manchester Metropolitan University. From his first placement during his studies Chris has been involved in large scale master planning and urban design projects from greenfield locations to industrial brown-field sites. In many of these projects sustainable issues and environmental responsibility have played a major role from aspects of rain and waste water management to integrated solar and wind energy possibilities. \n\nDuring two years in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia, Chris undertook research into aspects of eco-architecture, sustainability and urban growth and renewal in often challenging circumstances. Recently Chris has been involved in various stakeholder workshops where his skills of strategic thinking and ability to translate discussions into visual communications, have been utilised and greatly appreciated by those involved.",
